# Decision

Adopt **Option C: OKF substrate + Forge lifecycle engine + one-way promotion**.

- **OKF** (`.okf/`) is the Git-native curated memory substrate.
- **Forge MCPs** are the lifecycle planning engine — typed workspaces, signed packets, stage gates.
- **Promotion** from Forge to OKF is one-way, agent-mediated, and review-gated.

Forge is enabled on a **product project** after OKF five-service setup. It is not part of the default bootstrap layer.

# Operational flow

```text
Read OKF → invoke Forge MCP (planning) → promote to OKF (integrator review)
         → OKF dispatch (implementation) → log / handoff
```

# Consequences

- Operator guide: `docs/forge-lifecycle-integration.md`
- Forge workspaces live under `.okf/forge/` (gitignored) until promoted
- Sibling Forge repos are cloned separately — not vendored in this repository

